urls.expanded_url_title: Chloé Zhao Becomes the first Asian-American Woman to win the Golden Globe for Best Director
urls.expanded_url_description: Chloé Zhao accepts the award for best director, motion picture. Credit... NBC Chloé Zhao, whose drama “Nomadland” offered an intimate portrait of itinerant Americans, won the Golden Globe for best director on Sunday, making her the first Asian-American woman ever to win that prize. Earlier in the night, Zhao had also been nominated in the best screenplay” category.
